value.value: セメント細胞の形態異常

any structural anomaly of an apparently terminally differentiated cementoblast that has become embedded in the cellular cementum in a small cavity called lacuna and that extends long cytoplasmic (dendritic) processes away from the cell body toward other cementocytes and neighboring cells in small channels called canaliculi
セメント細胞小腔の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the small cavity within the cellular cementum that is occupied by a cementocyte cell body; cementocyte lacunae are described as larger and more irregular in size and shape (from oval to tubular) and with rougher walls than the typical ellipsoid osteocyte lacunae; occasionally, empty lacunae or lacunae containing more than one cell are observed in cellular cementum, not typically observed in osteocyte lacunae
セメント細胞細管の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the slender canals situated between lacunae of the cellular cementum where cementocyte cytoplasmic (dendritic) processes reside; cementocyte canaliculi appear to be less organized, more sparse, and do they radiate outward, with the majority of them oriented toward the vascular periodontal ligament for nutrition, unlike osteocyte canaliculi which are radiating, more dense and arranged in a complex network
セメント細胞樹状突起の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the long, slender cytoplasmic processes that extend from the cementocyte cell body, run along narrow canaliculi, and are linked to neighboring cementocytes processes via gap junctions; cementocytes harbor fewer dendritic processes than osteocytes
上咽頭欠如
failure to form the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate
歯髄根管形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the dental pulp cavity within the root of a tooth
歯髄根管肥大
increased size of the portion of the dental pulp cavity within the root of a tooth
歯髄室形態異常
any structural anomaly of the portion of the dental pulp cavity within the crown of a tooth
歯髄室形態肥大
increased size of the portion of the dental pulp cavity within the crown of a tooth
歯周靭帯剥離
partial or complete loss of attachment of the periodontal ligament to the cementum covering the root of a tooth
心筋緻密層の厚化
increased thickness of the outer, dense layer of the myocardium
アンモニア血中濃度低下
reduced concentration of ammonia or its compounds in the blood
A帯形態異常

any structural anomaly of the dark-staining region of a sarcomere that is situated between two I bands and marked by partial overlapping of thin (actin) and thick (myosin) filaments; an A band is anisotropic to polarized light and contains the entire length of a single thick filament; its center is traversed by the paler H zone, which in turn contains the M line
I帯形態異常

any structural anomaly of the light band on each side of the Z disc (aka Z line), comprising a region of the sarcomere where thin (actin) filaments are not overlapped by thick (myosin) filaments; the I band is isotropic to polarized light and contains actin, troponin, and tropomyosin; each sarcomere includes half of an I band at each end
Hゾーン形態異常

any structural anomaly of the relatively pale zone traversing the center of the A band of a sarcomere, visible in relaxed muscle fibers; it consists of the central portion of thick (myosin) filaments that are not overlapped by thin (actin) filaments; within the H zone is a thin dark M line, the attachment site for the thick filaments in the center of the sarcomere
糸球体毛細血管内皮症
a renal lesion characterized by glomerular endothelial swelling with glomerular hypertrophy, obliteration of endothelial fenestrae, and narrowing or occlusion of the capillary lumens
毛管形態異常
any structural anomaly of the tubular connection that is found between the epidermal surface and the most distal part of the hair follicle inner root sheath and contains the hair shaft
毛管拡張

stretched or widened aperture of the luminal space of the tubular connection that is found between the epidermal surface and the most distal part of the hair follicle inner root sheath and contains the hair shaft; the infundibulum is the opening of the hair canal to the skin surface
毛嚢脂腺ユニット形態異常
any structural anomaly of an epidermal invagination consisting of hair, hair follicle, arrector pili muscle and sebaceous gland
毛包細胞増殖異常
anomaly in the ability of any hair follicle cell population to undergo expansion by cell division
毛包細胞増殖増加
increase in the expansion rate of a hair follicle cell population by cell division
毛包細胞増殖の低下
reduction in the expansion rate of a hair follicle cell population by cell division
ケラチノサイト付着異常
any anomaly in the adhesive properties of keratinocytes, resulting in abnormal cell to cell and cell to extracellular matrix (ECM) interactions
ケラチノサイト付着増加
increased ability of a keratinocyte to adhere to another cell or to a non-cellular component of the environment
ケラチノサイト付着減少
decreased ability of a keratinocyte to adhere to another cell or to a non-cellular component of the environment
胸腹壁破裂症
a congenital fissure of both the thoracic and abdominal walls
毛包肥厚板形態異常

any structural anomaly of any of the local epithelial thickenings in the embryonic epidermis that define the location of the hair follicles; in mouse, embryonic hair follicle development is initiated by the first dermal signal, originating from dermal fibroblasts, leading to the formation of placodes at ~E13.5; each placode sends a message back to underlying dermis, which results in the formation of an aggregate of mesenchymal cells known as the dermal condensate; the placodes then grow downward, giving rise to the hair germ by E15.5, the hair peg by E17.5, and the bulbous hair peg by E18.5
毛包肥厚板欠如
absence of the local epithelial thickening in the embryonic epidermis that normally gives rise to the hair follicle bud (aka hair germ)
毛包肥厚板形成異常

any anomaly in the developmental process in which a hair placode forms; in mouse, hair placode formation is initiated at ~E13.5 in response to the first dermal signal originating from dermal fibroblasts; the resulting primary hair placode cells signal to the underlying dermis, triggering formation of dermal condensates that will coordinate further differentiation of hair-forming cells; hair placode formation progresses through 3 successive waves (1) primary hair placodes form at E14.5 and produce guard hair, (2) secondary hair placodes form at E16-17 and produce awl hair, and (3) the third wave of hair follicle induction produces tertiary placodes and generate zig-zag hair
毛包ペグ形態異常

any structural anomaly of the solid column of keratinocytes growing into the dermis during embryonic hair follicle development; the concave proximal end starts to encase the dermal condensate, the future dermal papilla
皮膚萎縮

acquired diminution of skin tissue associated with wasting as from death and reabsorption of cells, diminished cellular proliferation, decreased cellular volume, pressure, ischemia, malnutrition, reduced function or malfunction, or hormonal changes
アンフェタミンに対する行動反応の増強

increased sensitivity to amphetamine resulting in a behavioral response, such as induced hyperactivity or stereotypic behavior, or decreased dosage threshold for the appearance of the behavioral response
アンフェタミンに対する行動反応障害

decreased sensitivity to amphetamine resulting in a behavioral response, such as induced hyperactivity or stereotypic behavior, or increased dosage threshold for the appearance of the behavioral response
膵臓α細胞集団異常
anomaly in the total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic alpha cell compared to the normal state
膵臓α細胞集団減少
reduced total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic alpha cell compared to the normal state
膵臓α細胞集団増加
greater total physical bulk or volume of a pancreatic alpha cell compared to the normal state
精子線維鞘形態異常

any structural anomaly of the unique cytoskeletal component in the principal-piece segment of the sperm flagellum which surrounds the axoneme and outer dense fibers and contains two longitudinal columns that are connected by closely organized semicircular transverse ribs; the fibrous sheath is believed to regulate the degree of flexibility, flagellar motion and shape of the flagellar beat during the lifespan of a sperm cell
精子線維鞘欠損

missing the unique cytoskeletal component of the principal-piece segment of the sperm flagellum which surrounds the axoneme and outer dense fibers and contains two longitudinal columns that are connected by closely organized semicircular transverse ribs
マンガン恒常性異常

anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of manganese ions within an organism or cell; manganese ions function as cofactors for a large variety of enzymes with many functions; while the element is a required trace mineral for all known living organisms, it also acts as a neurotoxin in larger amounts
マンガン濃度異常
any anomaly in the concentration of manganese in the body
脳内マンガン値異常
any anomaly in the amount of manganese present in brain tissue
脳内マンガン濃度上昇
a greater accumulation of manganese in brain tissue compared to controls
脳内マンガン値低下
a reduced amount of manganese in brain tissue compared to controls
肝臓内マンガン値異常
any anomaly in the amount of manganese present in liver tissue
肝臓内マンガン値上昇
a greater accumulation of manganese in liver tissue compared to controls
肝臓内マンガン値低下
a reduced amount of manganese in liver tissue compared to controls
マンガン血中濃度異常
any anomaly in the blood concentration of manganese
マンガン血中濃度上昇
greater than normal concentration of manganese in the blood
マンガン血中濃度低下
less than the normal concentration of manganese in the blood
精子数の増加
increased concentration of spermatozoa in the seminal fluid
